This paper deals with the problem of interference management in a communication network, which is a fundamental problem in information theory and communication engineering. The paper proposes a decentralized approach to interference management, where each transmitter-receiver pair autonomously tunes its own transmit-receive configurations seeking an $\eta$-optimal individual transmission rate. This problem falls under the category of decentralized control and optimization, which is a subfield of control theory and optimization. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.IT (Information Theory). 

The paper also deals with the problem of feedback in the interference channel, which is a subfield of networked control systems and communication networks. Therefore, the paper may also belong to the sub-categories cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). 

The paper uses mathematical optimization techniques to approximate the $\eta$-Nash equilibrium region of the interference channel, which is a subfield of mathematical optimization and game theory. Therefore, the paper may also belong to the sub-categories cs.MM (Mathematical Optimization) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
